<body>
    <header>
        <h1>How to Make the Perfect Layer Cake</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Introduction</h2>
            <p>Are you ready to elevate your baking game? This guide will show you how to create a professional-quality layer cake from scratch. From selecting the right ingredients to perfecting your frosting techniques, this step-by-step guide ensures your cake is as delicious as it is beautiful.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Ingredients and Tools</h2>
            <h3>Ingredients</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>2 ½ cups cake flour</li>
                <li>1 cup unsalted butter, softened</li>
                <li>1 ¾ cups sugar</li>
                <li>4 large eggs</li>
                <li>1 cup whole milk</li>
                <li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
                <li>2 teaspoons baking powder</li>
                <li>½ teaspoon salt</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Tools</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Mixing bowls</li>
                <li>Electric mixer</li>
                <li>Cake pans (two 8-inch or 9-inch)</li>
                <li>Spatula</li>
                <li>Cooling rack</li>
                <li>Offset spatula or butter knife</li>
                <li>Piping bags (optional)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Step-by-Step Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Preheat the Oven and Prepare Pans</strong>
                    <p>Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and line your cake pans with parchment paper.</p>
                    <img src="https://brighteyedbaker.com/2013/10/29/chocolate-chai-layer-cake/" alt="Preparing pans">
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Mix the Batter</strong>
                    <p>Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, then mix in vanilla. Alternate adding dry ingredients and milk, starting and ending with the dry mix.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Divide and Bake</strong>
                    <p>Divide batter evenly between pans. Bake for 25–35 minutes or until a skewer comes out clean. Cool completely on a wire rack.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Level and Frost</strong>
                    <p>Level the cake layers with a serrated knife. Apply a thin crumb coat before adding the final layer of frosting.</p>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mWItHfoJe_A" target="_blank">Watch crumb coating tutorial</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Decorate</strong>
                    <p>Use piping bags and spatulas to add decorative details. For inspiration, check out these <a href="https://mytrendyfoods.blogspot.com/2023/01/cake-decorating-techniques-pdf-basic.html" target="_blank">cake decorating tips</a>.</p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Tips for Success</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Grease generously: Prevent sticking by thoroughly greasing your pans.</li>
                <li>Measure accurately: Use a kitchen scale for precise measurements.</li>
                <li>Cool completely: Avoid frosting warm cakes to prevent melting.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>References</h2>
